ns1:Book2c7990a3-5c4f-4b68-8797-480d371e474f a ns1:Book ;
    ns1:author "Kate Petty" ;
    pbs:constellationLink "https://constellations.education.gouv.qc.ca/index.php?p=il&lo=52487" ;
    ns1:datePublished "2006"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns1:publisher "Quarto"^^xsd:string ;
    ns1:reviewBody """Home in Cambodia might be a house on stilts; in Mauritania, it could be made of clay. Xin’s home in China is carved from rock. This sturdy Oxfam-sponsored book features examples of a variety of homes around the world. \r
Each large, colourful photograph is accompanied by a short, large-print text that gives some interesting details about the house and the country in which it is found. \r
The children in each picture comment on their home via dialogue bubbles: “I have to crouch down to get in!” says Aluka of Uganda. “Our caravan is our home wherever we stop.” explains Yanni of Romania.\r
At the end, a labelled world map pinpoints the location of the 11 different homes presented. \r
\r
This soft-board non-fiction book will have children reflecting on how homes are determined by climate, culture and geography. But whether it is brick or earth, rounded or flat-topped, built to warm or built to cool, home is always where a child’s heart is.""" ;
