ns1:Book3067b7a0-9cf3-4ba7-a3f5-ca0b7cc49225 a ns1:Book ;
    ns1:author "Erin Entrada Kelly" ;
    pbs:constellationLink "https://constellations.education.gouv.qc.ca/index.php?p=il&lo=54021" ;
    ns1:datePublished "2017"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns1:publisher ns1:HarperCollins ;
    ns1:reviewBody """Virgil Salinas is small, shy and quiet. Few people know him well other than his eagle-eyed grandmother and his friend Kaori Tanaka. Kaori believes deeply in astrology and fate and pledges to help Virgil meet the girl of his destiny, the mysterious V.S. Valencia Somerset, meanwhile, is a smart girl whose trusting nature has been curbed by discrimination—she is deaf and has been spurned by her peers. Both Virgil and Valencia are frequent victims of Chet “the Bull”, the school bully. As becomes clear when readers are introduced to Chet’s father, the boy’s mean streak may be a learned defense mechanism.  \r
\r
Virgil is on his way to Kaori’s when Chet intercepts him in the woods and throws his backpack down a well. Gullliver, Virgil’s guinea pig, is in the bag. The boy climbs down the well to save his pet but can’t get back out. Crossing the woods a little later, Valencia notices the open well and, unable to hear Virgil’s calls for help, closes the lid. Once they realize Virgil is missing, Kaori, Valencia and Kaori’s sister, Gen, pool their instinct, knowledge and powers of deduction to find and save their friend. \r
\r
The novel pays close third-person attention to each of the main characters, allowing readers insight into Virgil’s fearful nature and his reserve of unknown courage, Valencia’s painful rejection by her friends and Kaori’s visionary loyalty, both to her friends and to her esoteric beliefs.  \r
\r
The narrative is fast paced; short action scenes are propelled by dialogue. Even Virgil’s time in the darkness of the lidded well conjures up an interlocutor out of one of his grandmother’s stories about a child who didn’t know her destiny.""" ;
