    ns1:datePublished "2013"^^xsd:gYear ;
    ns1:publisher ns1:Penguin_Random_House ;
    ns1:reviewBody """In this monochromatic wordless story, a bluebird befriends a sad and lonely boy, follows him to school and hangs out with him against the backdrop of New York City. \r
\r
When the boy encounters a group of bullies and the bluebird protects him from harm, one of the mean boys strikes the bird with a stick. \r
\r
What could be a troubling ending is ultimately poignant and open-ended, involving a myriad rainbow of birds and the reader's own imagination.\r
\r
Simple and evocative, this picture book is laid out in the style of a graphic novel with blue-, grey- and black-hued illustrations that deftly capture the emotions of a lonely and friendless boy who finally finds companionship. \r
\r
Its wordless portrayal of the timeless and universal experiences of loneliness, bullying, friendship and hope will resonate with readers young and old.""" ;
